HIV/AIDS: China ta samu karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na sababbin kamuwa da cutar
Kasar Sin ta ba da rahoton karuwar kashi 14 cikin 100 na yawan mutanen kasar Sin da ke fama da cutar HIV da AIDS.
Mutane fiye da 820,000 ne suka kamu da cutar a kasar Sin, jami'ai sun ce.
An samu sababbin shari'o'i kusan 40,000 a cikin wata uku na 2018 kawai.
Yawancin sababbin cututtuka sun kasance na jima'i, ba kamar na baya ba.
A dā, cutar HIV ta yi ta yaduwa a wasu yankunan ƙasar Sin sakamakon ƙarin jini da aka yi wa mutane.
Amma adadin mutanen da suka kamu da cutar ta HIV ta wannan hanyar ya ragu zuwa kusan sifili, in ji jami'an kiwon lafiya na kasar Sin a wani taro a lardin Yunnan.
Amma, a shekara guda, adadin mutanen da ke da cutar HIV da AIDS a kasar Sin ya ƙaru da mutane 100,000.
Cutar HIV ta hanyar jima'i babbar matsala ce a cikin al'ummar LGBT a kasar Sin.
An yi watsi da jima'i a kasar Sin a shekara ta 1997, amma ana ganin nuna bambanci ga 'yan luwadi a duniya.
Domin al'adun kasar, bincike ya nuna cewa kashi 70 zuwa 90 cikin 100 na maza da suke yin jima'i da maza za su auri mace.
Yawancin cututtuka na cututtuka sun fito ne daga rashin kariya ta jima'i a irin wannan dangantaka.
Tun shekara ta 2003, gwamnatin kasar Sin ta yi alkawarin samun damar yin amfani da magungunan HIV a duniya a matsayin wani ɓangare na ƙoƙarin magance matsalar.
